            HEXADECIMAL BASE


    HEXADECIMAL BASE or Base 16.
    HEXADECIMAL BASE uses numbers
    0..15.  Letters a..f represent
    numbers 10..15.  When in HEXA-
    DECIMAL BASE, HEX appears on
    the left side of the screen.
    The maximum number in decimal 
    that may be used is 268435455
    plus or minus.  See BASE 
    SYSTEM on how to convert between
    the bases.
